                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">White</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Hay</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Embassy of the United States</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">London</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1903-01-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">January 26, 1903</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>(Mr. White reports that he finds at the foreign office and at the prime
                    minister’s office hopeful view of an early settlement; that Mr. Bowen’s
                    arrangements for payment of first claims are satisfactory, and the only obstacle
                    now, apparently, is the desire of the three allied powers to secure priority for
                    their claims upon Venezuelan customs over those of other powers. The British
                    Government is making strenuous efforts to get settlement sufficiently advanced
                    to raise the blockade, which Mr. White understands may be on January 27 or
                    28.)</p>
            </div>
        </body>
